OL,3,CMother of son who died of undiagnosed
OL,4,Ceating disorder urges NHS to act
OL,6,FAfter his death he was diagnosed with
OL,7,FArfid, a condition that has been
OL,8,Frecognised for more than 10 years but
OL,9,Fone that has no national guidelines
OL,10,Fabout how best to treat it.
OL,12,FLucy Morrison said: "When it came to
OL,13,Feating food with textures and lumps,
OL,14,FAlfie would gag on the food. He would
OL,15,Freally get distressed. That's once you
OL,16,Fgot the food in his mouth. Even food
OL,17,Fin front of him could cause him to be
OL,18,Fvery distressed.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G2/11
