OL,3,CMother of son who died of undiagnosed
OL,4,Ceating disorder urges NHS to act
OL,6,F"I always made it clear to every
OL,7,Fsingle professional it's because Alfie
OL,8,Fdoesn't eat right. As a parent, you're
OL,9,Fconstantly battling and asking for
OL,10,Fsupport and you're just left to do it
OL,11,Fon your own. I felt like I wasn't
OL,12,Fbelieved like I was going crazy."
OL,14,FAn inquest into Alfie's death which
OL,15,Fwas held last month in Stockport found
OL,16,Fthere was a lack of communication and
OL,17,Fprofessional curiosity about the
OL,18,Fnutritional value of his diet.
